A candidate backed by an ``InstallRequirement``.
This represents a package request with the target not being already in the environment, and needs to be fetched and installed. The backing ``InstallRequirement`` is responsible for most of the leg work; this class exposes appropriate information to the resolver.
:param link: The link passed to the ``InstallRequirement``. The backing ``InstallRequirement`` will use this link to fetch the distribution. :param source_link: The link this candidate "originates" from. This is different from ``link`` when the link is found in the wheel cache. ``link`` would point to the wheel cache, while this points to the found remote link (e.g. from pypi.org).
